+
+**When to Apply:**
+This profile governs ALL runtime text generation for any L. Frank Baum IP. It applies during: narrative generation, dialogue writing, scene description, choice-point text, branch resolution prose, and any player-facing text.
+
+**Feeds Into:**
+- Phase 2 (character voice reference)
+- Phase 5 (authored prose in choices)
+- Runtime Narrator Template (voice DNA, ban list, and 14-point audit protocol -- all loaded into the runtime narrator's system prompt for live self-audit during narration)
+
+**Interaction with Per-IP Extraction:**
+Per-IP extraction captures story-specific patterns (character speech habits, location vocabulary, plot-specific language). This author-level profile captures cross-story DNA. When they conflict, this profile wins -- the author's voice is more fundamental than any single story's patterns.
+
+**Runtime Audit Frequency:**
+The 14-Point Audit Protocol is loaded into the runtime narrator's system prompt. The runtime narrator runs it as a continuous self-audit on EVERY passage it generates -- narration, dialogue, scene description, choice-point text, branch resolution prose. All must pass all 14 checkpoints before reaching the player.
+
+**Corpus Note:**
+This profile is extracted from 5 Oz novels (The Wonderful Wizard of Oz, The Marvelous Land of Oz, Ozma of Oz, The Road to Oz, The Emerald City of Oz), totaling 211,398 words. Baum wrote 14 Oz novels total plus numerous non-Oz works. The techniques identified here are consistent across all 5 novels analyzed but may not capture the full range of later-period Baum. If additional texts become available, this profile should be expanded.
+
+=== END VOICE PROFILE ===
